ATTRIBUTION AND PRIOR ART NOTICE

This work establishes prior art for the following contributions. Any use,
reproduction, derivative work, or reference to the contents of this repository
must include attribution to the original authors as specified below.

1. STRUCTURED DISCOVERY PROTOCOL

   The structured discovery state tracking method described in this repository,
   including but not limited to: treating proof search as navigation over an
   explicit ignorance partition; the four-gate measurement framework (assumption
   compliance, inference validity, goal completion, generalization robustness);
   the structured ignorance log; and the ignorance narrowing dynamics (diffuse
   uncertainty to precise hypothesis spaces to incompleteness estimates), is the
   original work of Dhruv Gupta and Samanway.

2. AUDITED PROOF ATTEMPTS AND DATASET

   The 85 audited proof steps, 10 proof-level rollups, process traces, and
   cross-problem patterns contained in this repository are the original work
   of Dhruv Gupta and Samanway. The proofs were publicly archived at
   doi:10.5281/zenodo.18629234 before official solutions to the First Proof
   benchmark were released.

3. PROOF DOCUMENTS

   The proof attempt documents (zetesis_proof_attempt_P1.pdf through
   zetesis_proof_attempt_P10.pdf) are the original work of Dhruv Gupta and
   Samanway, produced autonomously via the structured discovery protocol
   described above.

